b-based with easy tools)\n\nUsing these programs, you can draw, paint, or import images to create your shirt design.\n\n<h3>3. A Roblox Account with Premium Membership<\/h3>\n\nTo upload and sell shirts on Roblox, you must have a Roblox Premium membership. This membership lets you upload custom clothing items and earn Robux from sales.\n\n<h2>Step-by-Step Guide: How to Create at Shirt on Roblox<\/h2>\n\n<h3>Step 1: Download the Shirt Template<\/h3>\n\nStart by grabbing the official shirt template. This template serves as your canvas and helps you understand where each part of the shirt will appear on your avatar. Make sure to save it in a format compatible with your image editing software, such as PNG.\n\n<h3>Step 2: Design Your Shirt<\/h3>\n\nOpen the template in your chosen editing program. Here are some tips to consider while designing:\n\n- Use layers to separate different elements of your design, making it easier to edit.\n- Pay close attention to the areas representing the torso, sleeves, and back to ensure your design aligns properly.\n- Keep the resolution at 585 x 559 pixels (the size of the Roblox shirt template).\n- Experiment with colors, patterns, and even text to make your shirt unique.\n- Avoid placing important details on the edges of each section, as they might stretch or warp when applied to the avatar.\n\n<h3>Step 3: Save and Export Your Design<\/h3>\n\nOnce you’re satisfied with your design, save the file as a PNG to preserve transparency and image quality. Ensure the file size complies with Roblox’s upload requirements to prevent errors.\n\n<h3>Step 4: Upload Your Shirt to Roblox<\/h3>\n\nNow, log in to your Roblox account and head over to the **Create** section in the navigation bar. Under **My Creations**, select **Shirts** and click the **Choose File** button to upload your PNG design.\n\nGive your shirt a catchy and descriptive name. This title will help others find your shirt if you decide to sell it in the marketplace. After naming, click 